  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Destruction in Israel and Judah'
      title: Destruction in Israel and Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the Lord that came to Micah of Moresheth in the days
        of Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah, which he saw [through divine
        revelation] concerning Samaria and Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hear, O peoples, all of you;Listen closely, O earth and all that
        is in it,And let the Lord God be witness [giving a testimony of the judgment]
        against you,The Lord from His holy temple [in the heavens].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For behold, the Lord is coming down from His placeHe shall come down
        and tread [in judgment] on the high places of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The mountains shall melt under HimAnd the valleys shall be splitLike
        wax before the fire,Like waters poured down a steep place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All this is because of the rebellion and apostasy of JacobAnd for
        the sins of the house of Israel (the Northern Kingdom).What is the rebellion
        and apostasy of Jacob?Is it not [the abandonment of God in order to worship
        the idols of] Samaria?What are the high places [of idolatry] in Judah (the
        Southern Kingdom)?Are they not Jerusalem [the capital and center of corruption]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore I [the Lord] shall make Samaria a heap of ruins [and of
        stones and arable land] in the open country,A place for planting vineyards;And
        I will pour her stones down into the ravineAnd lay bare her foundations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All her idols shall be broken in pieces,All her earnings [from her
        idolatry] shall be burned with fire,And all her images I shall make desolate;For
        from the earnings of a prostitute she collected them,And to the earnings
        of a prostitute they shall return.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Because of this I [Micah] must lament (mourn over with expressions
        of grief) and wail,I must go barefoot and naked [without outer garments as
        if robbed];I must wail like the jackalsAnd lament [with a loud, mournful
        cry] like the ostriches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For Samaria\u2019s wound is incurable,For it has come to Judah;The
        enemy has reached the gate of my people,Even to Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Announce it not in Gath [in Philistia],Weep not at all [and in
        this way betray your grief to Gentiles];In Beth-le-aphrah (House of Dust)
        roll in the dust [among your own people].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Go on your way [into exile\u2014stripped of beauty, disarmed], inhabitants
        of Shaphir (Beautiful), in shameful nakedness.The inhabitant of Zaanan (Go
        Out) does not go out [of the house];The wailing of Beth-ezel (House of Removal)
        will take away from you its support.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the inhabitant of Maroth (Bitterness)Writhes in pain [at its
        losses] and waits anxiously for good,Because a catastrophe has come down
        from the LordTo the gate of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Harness the chariot to the team of horses [to escape the invasion],O
        inhabitant of Lachish\u2014She was the beginning of sinTo the Daughter of
        Zion (Jerusalem)\u2014Because in you were foundThe rebellious acts of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore you will give parting giftsOn behalf of Moresheth-gath
        (Micah\u2019s home);The houses of Achzib (Place of Deceit) will become a
        deceptionTo the kings of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Moreover, I will bring on youThe one who takes possession,O inhabitant
        of Mareshah (Prominent Place).The glory (nobility) of Israel will enter Adullam
        [seeking refuge].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Make yourself bald [in mourning]\u2014shave off your hairFor the
        children of your delight;Remain as bald as the eagle,For your children will
        be taken from you into exile."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woe to Oppressors'
      title: Woe to Oppressors
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe (judgment is coming) to those who devise wickednessAnd plot
        evil on their beds!When morning comes, they practice evilBecause it is in
        the power of their hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They covet fields and seize them,And houses, and take them away.They
        oppress and rob a man and his house,A man and his inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord,\u201CBehold, I am planning against
        this family a disaster (exile)[Like a noose] from which you cannot remove
        your necks;Nor will you be able to walk haughtily and erect,For it will be
        an evil time [of subjugation to the invaders].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "On that day they shall take up a [taunting, deriding] parable against
        youAnd wail with a doleful and bitter song of mourning and say,\u2018We are
        completely destroyed!God exchanges the inheritance of my people;How He removes
        it from me!He divides our fields to the rebellious [our captors].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore, you will have no one stretching a measuring line [dividing
        the common land]For you by lot in the assembly of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018Do not speak out,\u2019 so they speak out.  But if they do
        not speak out concerning these things,Reproaches will not be turned back.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Is it being said, O house of Jacob:\u2018Is the Spirit of the Lord
        impatient?Or are these [prophesied judgments] His doings?\u2019Do not My
        words do goodTo the one walking uprightly?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But lately My people have stood up as an enemy [and have made Me
        their antagonist].You strip the ornaments off the garmentOf those unsuspecting
        passers-by,Like those returned from war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You evict the women (widows) of My people,Each one from her pleasant
        house;From her [young, fatherless] children you take away My splendor and
        blessing forever [by putting them among the pagans, away from Me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Arise and depart [because the captivity is inevitable],For this [land]
        is not the place of restBecause of the defilement that brings destruction,A
        painful and terrible destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "If a man walking in a false spirit [spouting deception]Should lie
        and say,\u2018I will prophesy to you [O Israel] of wine and liquor (greed,
        sensual pleasure),\u2019He would be the acceptable spokesman of this people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI shall most certainly assemble all of you, O Jacob;I shall
        surely gather the remnant of Israel.I shall bring them together like sheep
        in the fold [multiplying the nation];Like a flock in the midst of its pasture.The
        place will swarm with many people and hum loudly with noise.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The breaker [the Messiah, who opens the way] shall go up before them
        [liberating them].They will break out, pass through the gate and go out;So
        their King goes on before them,The Lord at their head.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rulers Denounced'
      title: Rulers Denounced
      number: 1
      content: "  And I said,\u201CHear now, heads of JacobAnd rulers of the house
        of Israel.Is it not for you to know and administer justice?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You who hate good and love evil,Who tear the skin off my peopleAnd
        their flesh from their bones;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You who eat the flesh of my people,Strip off their skin from them,Break
        their bonesAnd chop them in pieces as for the pot,Like meat in a kettle.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then they will cry to the Lord,But He will not answer them;Instead,
        He will even hide His face from them at that time [withholding His mercy]Because
        they have practiced and tolerated and ignored evil acts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says the Lord concerning the [false] prophets who lead my people
        astray;When they have something good to bite with their teeth,They call out,
        \u201CPeace,\u201DBut against the one who gives them nothing to eat,They
        declare a holy war.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore it will be night (tragedy) for you\u2014without vision,And
        darkness (cataclysm) for you\u2014without foresight.The sun shall go down
        on the [false] prophets,And the day shall become dark and black over them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The seers shall be ashamedAnd the diviners discredited and embarrassed;Indeed,
        they shall all cover their mouths [in shame]Because there is no answer from
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But in fact, I am filled with power,With the Spirit of the Lord,And
        with justice and might,To declare to Jacob his transgressionAnd to Israel
        his sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now hear this, you heads of the house of JacobAnd rulers of the house
        of Israel,Who hate and reject justiceAnd twist everything that is straight,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who build Zion with blood [and extortion and murder]And Jerusalem
        with violent injustice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Her leaders pronounce judgment for a bribe,Her priests teach for
        a fee,And her prophets foretell for money;Yet they lean on the Lord, saying,\u201CIs
        not the Lord among us?No tragedy or distress will come on us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Therefore, on account of you  Zion shall be plowed like a field,Jerusalem
        shall become a heap of ruins,And the mountain of the house [of the Lord]
        shall become like a densely wooded hill.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Peaceful Latter Days'
      title: Peaceful Latter Days
      number: 1
      content: '  But it shall come about in the last daysThat the mountain of the
        house of the LordShall be established as the highest and chief of the mountains;It
        shall be above the hills,And peoples shall flow [like a river] to it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And many nations shall come and say,\u201CCome, let us go up to the
        mountain of the Lord,To the house of the God of Jacob,That He may teach us
        about His waysAnd that we may walk in His paths.\u201DFor the law shall go
        forward from Zion,And the word of the Lord [the revelation about Him and
        His truth] from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And He will judge between many peoplesAnd render decisions for strong
        and distant nations.Then they shall hammer their swords into plowsharesAnd
        their spears into pruning hooks [so that the implements of war may become
        the tools of agriculture];Nation shall not lift up sword against nation,Nor
        shall they ever again train for war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Each of them shall sit [in security and peace] under his vineAnd
        under his fig tree,With no one to make them afraid,For the mouth of the [omnipotent]
        Lord of hosts has spoken it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For all the peoples [now] walkEach in the name of his god [in a transient
        relationship],As for us, we shall walk [securely]In the name of the Lord
        our [true] God forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CI shall assemble the
        lame,And gather the outcasts [from foreign captivity],Even those whom I have
        caused pain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I shall make the lame a [godly] remnantAnd the outcasts a strong
        nation;And the Lord shall reign over them in Mount ZionFrom this time on
        and forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "As for you [Jerusalem], tower of the flock [of Israel],Hill and stronghold
        of the Daughter of Zion (Jerusalem\u2019s inhabitants),To you the former
        dominion shall come,The kingdom of the Daughter of Jerusalem [when the Messiah
        reigns in Jerusalem, and the times of the Gentiles are fulfilled].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CNow, why do you cry out loudly?Is there no king among you?Has
        your counselor perished?For agony has gripped you like a woman in childbirth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Writhe in pain and labor to give birth,O Daughter of Zion,Like a
        woman in childbirth;For now you shall go out of the city,Live in the field,And
        go to Babylon.There you will be rescued;There the Lord shall redeem youFrom
        the hand of your enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now many [conquering] nations are assembled against you,Who say,
        \u2018Let her be profaned [through Gentile presence and the temple\u2019s
        destruction],And let our eyes gaze on and gloat over Zion.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But they (Gentile nations) do not know the thoughts of the Lord,Nor
        do they understand His purpose and plan;For He has gathered them (Gentiles)
        like sheaves to the threshing floor [for destruction].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Arise and thresh, O Daughter of Zion!For I will make your horn ironAnd
        I will make your hoofs bronze;That you may beat many peoples in pieces [trampling
        down your enemies],That you may devote to the Lord their unjust gain (pagan
        possessions)And their wealth to the Lord of all the earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Birth of the King in Bethlehem'
      title: Birth of the King in Bethlehem
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNow gather yourself in troops, O daughter of troops;A state
        of siege has been placed against us.They shall strike the ruler of Israel
        on the cheek with a rod (scepter).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But as for you, Bethlehem Ephrathah,Too little to be among the clans
        of Judah;From you One shall come forth for Me [who is] to be Ruler in Israel,His
        goings forth (appearances) are from long ago,From ancient days.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore, He will give them up until the timeWhen she who is in
        labor has given birth to a child.Then what is left of His kinsmenShall return
        to the children of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And He shall stand and shepherd and guide His flockIn the strength
        of the Lord,In the majesty of the name of the Lord His God;And they shall
        dwell [secure in undisturbed peace],Because at that time He shall be great
        [extending His authority][Even] to the ends of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'This One [the Messiah] shall be our peace.  When the Assyrian invades
        our landAnd tramples on our citadels and in our palaces,Then shall we raise
        against himSeven shepherds and eight princes [an overpowering force] among
        men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They shall devastate the land of Assyria with the sword andThe land
        of Nimrod within her [own] gates.And He (the Messiah) shall rescue us from
        the Assyrian (all enemy nations)When he attacks our landAnd when he tramples
        our territory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the remnant of JacobShall be among many peoplesLike dew from
        the Lord,Like showers on the grass [a source of blessing]Which [come suddenly
        and] do not wait for manNor delay for the sons of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The remnant of JacobShall be among the nations,In the midst of many
        peoplesLike a lion among the beasts of the forest,Like a young lion [suddenly
        appearing] among the flocks of sheepWhich, if he passes through,Tramples
        down and tears into pieces [the nations in judgment],And there is no one
        to rescue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Your hand will be lifted up against your adversaries,And all your
        enemies shall be cut off and destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd in that day,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CI will cut off your
        horses from among youAnd destroy your chariots [on which you depend].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I will cut off the cities of your landAnd tear down all your fortifications.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will cut off witchcrafts and sorceries from your hand,And you shall
        have no more fortune-tellers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will also cut off your carved imagesAnd your sacred pillars from
        among you,So that you will no longer worship and bow downTo the work of your
        hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will root out your Asherim (symbols of the goddess Asherah) from
        among youAnd destroy your cities [which are the centers of pagan worship].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And in anger and wrath I shall execute vengeanceOn the nations which
        have not obeyed [such vengeance as they have not known before].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Indictment of His People"
      title: "God\u2019s Indictment of His People"
      number: 1
      content: "  Hear now what the Lord is saying,\u201CArise, plead your case before
        the mountains,And let the hills [as witnesses] hear your voice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hear, O mountains, the indictment of the Lord,And you enduring foundations
        of the earth,For the Lord has a case (a legal complaint) against His people,And
        He will dispute (challenge) Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O My people, what have I done to you [since you have turned away
        from Me]?And how have I wearied you? Answer Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For I brought you up from the land of EgyptAnd ransomed you from
        the house of slavery,And I sent before you Moses [to lead you], Aaron [the
        high priest], and Miriam [the prophetess].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: What God Requires of Man'
      title: What God Requires of Man
      number: 5
      content: "My people, remember nowWhat Balak king of Moab devised [with his
        evil plan against Israel]And what Balaam the son of Beor answered him [turning
        the curse into blessing for Israel],[Remember what the Lord did for you]
        from Shittim to Gilgal,So that you may know the righteous and saving acts
        [displaying the power] of the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'With what shall I come before the Lord [to honor Him]And bow myself
        before God on high?Shall I come before Him with burnt offerings,With yearling
        calves?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Will the Lord be delighted with thousands of rams,Or with ten thousand
        rivers of oil?Shall I present my firstborn for my acts of rebellion,The fruit
        of my body for the sin of my soul?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He has told you, O man, what is good;And what does the Lord require
        of youExcept to be just, and to love [and to diligently practice] kindness
        (compassion),And to walk humbly with your God [setting aside any overblown
        sense of importance or self-righteousness]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The voice of the Lord shall call to the city [of Jerusalem]\u2014And
        it is sound wisdom to heed [solemnly] and fear Your name [with awe-filled
        reverence];\u201CHear, O tribe [the rod of punishment]. Who has appointed
        its time?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Are there not still treasures gained by wickednessIn the house of
        the wicked,And a short (inaccurate) measure [for grain] that is cursed?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Can I [be guiltless and] justify deceptive scalesAnd a bag of dishonest
        weights?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the rich men of the city are full of violence [of every kind];Her
        inhabitants speak liesAnd their tongue is deceitful in their mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So also I will make you sick, striking you down,Desolating and devastating
        you, because of your sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall eat, but you will not be satisfied,And your emptiness shall
        be among you;You will [try to] remove [your goods and those you love] for
        safekeepingBut you will fail to save anything,And what you do save I shall
        give to the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You shall sow but you shall not reap;You shall tread olives, but
        shall not anoint yourself with oil,And [you will extract juice from] the
        grapes, but you shall not drink the wine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For [you have kept] the statutes of Omri [the idolatrous king],And
        all the works of the [wicked] house (dynasty) of Ahab;And you walk in their
        counsels and policies.Therefore, I shall hand you over for destruction and
        horrorAnd your [city\u2019s] inhabitants for ridicule,And you shall bear
        the rebuke and scorn of My people.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Prophet Acknowledges Injustice'
      title: The Prophet Acknowledges Injustice
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe is me (judgment is coming)! For I amLike one who gathers the
        summer fruits, like one who gleans the vintage grapes.There is not a cluster
        of grapes to eat,No first-ripe fig which my appetite craves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The godly person [who is faithful and loyal to God] has perished
        from the earth,And there is no upright person [one with good character and
        moral integrity] among men.They all lie in wait to shed blood;Each hunts
        the other with a net.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Concerning evil, both of their hands pursue it and do it diligently
        and thoroughly;The prince asks, also the judge, for a bribe,And a great man
        speaks the [evil] desire of his soul.So they twist the course of justice
        between them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The best of them is [injurious] like a briar;The most upright is
        [prickly] like a thorn hedge.The day of your watchmen [that is, the time
        predicted by the prophets]And your punishment comes;Now shall be their confusion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do not trust in a neighbor [because of the moral corruption in the
        land];Do not have confidence in a friend.Guard the doors of your mouthFrom
        her who lies in your bosom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: God Is the Source of Salvation and Light'
      title: God Is the Source of Salvation and Light
      number: 6
      content: "For the son dishonors the father and treats him contemptuously,The
        daughter rises up [in hostility] against her mother,The daughter-in-law against
        her mother-in-law\u2014A man\u2019s enemies are the men (members) of his
        own household.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But as for me, I will look expectantly for the Lord  and with confidence
        in Him I will keep watch;I will wait [with confident expectation] for the
        God of my salvation.My God will hear me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Do not rejoice over me [amid my tragedies], O my enemy!Though I fall,
        I will rise;Though I sit in the darkness [of distress], the Lord is a light
        for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will bear the indignation and wrath of the LordBecause I have sinned
        against Him,Until He pleads my case and executes judgment for me.He will
        bring me out to the light,And I will behold His [amazing] righteousness and
        His remarkable deliverance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then my enemy [all the pagan nations] shall see it,And shame [for
        despising the Lord] will cover her who said to me,\u201CWhere is the Lord
        your God?\u201DMy eyes will look on her [with satisfaction at her judgment];Now
        she (unbelievers) will be trampled downLike mud of the streets.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  It shall be a day for building your walls,On that day the boundary
        [of Israel] shall be [greatly] extended.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'It shall be a day when the Gentiles will come to youFrom Assyria
        and from the cities of Egypt,And from Egypt even to the river Euphrates,From
        sea to sea and from mountain to mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet the earth [beyond the land of Israel] shall become desolate because
        of those who dwell in it,Because of the fruit of their deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Shepherd and rule Your people with Your scepter [of blessing],The
        flock of Your inheritance and Your possessionWhich dwells alone [separate
        and secure from attack] in the forest,In the midst of a garden land.Let them
        feed in Bashan and GileadAs in the days of old [the days of Moses and Elijah].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAs in the days when you came out from the land of Egypt,I shall
        show you marvelous and miraculous things.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The [pagan] nations shall see [God\u2019s omnipotence in delivering
        Israel] and be ashamedOf all their might [which cannot be compared to His].They
        shall put their hand on their mouth [in silent astonishment];Their ears shall
        be deaf.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They shall lick the dust like a serpent;Like crawling things of the
        earthThey shall come trembling out of their fortresses and hiding places.They
        shall turn and come with fear and dread to the Lord our GodAnd they shall
        be afraid and stand in awe before You [O Lord].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Who is a God like You, who forgives wickednessAnd passes over the
        rebellious acts of the remnant of His possession?He does not retain His anger
        forever,Because He [constantly] delights in mercy and lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He shall again have compassion on us;He will subdue and tread underfoot
        our wickedness [destroying sin\u2019s power].Yes, You will cast all our sinsInto
        the depths of the sea.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: You shall give truth to JacobAnd lovingkindness and mercy to Abraham,As
        You have sworn to our forefathersFrom the days of old.
      comments: []
